/*
# Clock click actions

Configure what happens when the Windows 11 taskbar clock is clicked with the
left, middle, or right mouse button.

Supported actions:

- Open Quick Settings.
- Open Notifications.
- Open an application, path, or URL.
- Do nothing.

Optionally, apply a custom color to text in the Windows system tray, including
the clock, date, language indicator, and text-based tray icons. The hidden-icons
arrow and image-based notification icons aren't changed.

The clock tooltip is hidden while the mod is active.

The click actions target the Windows 11 taskbar clock/notification button. The
text-color option targets the Windows system tray. The legacy Windows 10
taskbar isn't supported.

For custom targets, use values such as `notepad.exe`,
`C:\Windows\System32\calc.exe`, `C:\Users\Public`, `https://example.com`, or a
Windows URI such as `ms-settings:`.
*/
// ==/WindhawkModReadme==

